values:
"I know the pieces fit cause I watched them fall away"&nbsp; - Tool

We witness pieces that fall out of the puzzle everyday.&nbsp; We see friendships fall apart, broken families, poverty-stricken areas, and an HIV/AIDS epidemic claim the lives of millions. But do the pieces all indeed fit? Did they at one point fit together? I mean, it's easy to imagine broken friendships and families that were once harmonious, but the pieces of impoverished countries and the AIDS epidemic...did those ever fit together to create one giant peaceful whole? And just because we 'watched [the pieces] fall away', does that mean that they can be made to fit back together so that they won't fall? Is everything connected in world? Is there one underlying cause beneath all the pain, anger, and strife in the world? Some say money, some say egos, some say greed...do we really know what we're up against? I read in the papers that the two Bill's...Bill Clinton and Bill Gates...are pushing to put the AIDS epidemic at the top priority for governments and the UN funding. What are they intending to fund? Any funding will only temporarily MAYBE put a tiny DENT in the number of HIV+ people in third world countries. What these people with lots of money and power are forgetting to see, is the bigger picture - a giant puzzle.&nbsp;&nbsp;Authority&nbsp;issues,&nbsp;disease outbreaks, societal 'norms', behavioural problems...all of these things are mere pieces that make up one grand scheme - rooted in&nbsp;corporations,&nbsp;the ego, avarice, and above all, thirst for money.&nbsp;&nbsp;

I don't know, maybe i'm just...over-analyzing things...cause we all know that happens a lot *heh*&nbsp;

buuuuuuttt...then again...maybe things need to be over-analyzed dumdumdum (but then it fact it wouldn't be called "over"-analyzed because if that's what needed to be done then it'd just be plain ol' analyzing...but that's another story =D)
